Prompt Dependencies:
- types_TypeScript.prompt — provides `PipelineStage`, `StageStatus`

Instructions
- Define `STAGE_CONFIG: Array<{ stage: PipelineStage; label: string; number: number }>` constant with all 10 entries.
- `useEffect` with 5s interval: `const interval = setInterval(() => fetchStatus(), 5000); return () => clearInterval(interval)`.
- Fetch `/api/pipeline/status` and update `stageStatuses` state: `Record<PipelineStage, StageStatusEntry>`.
- Badge color classes: done=`text-stage-done`, running=`text-stage-running animate-stage-running`, error=`text-stage-error`, not_started=`text-stage-not-started`.
- Active stage row: `border-l-2 border-blue-400 bg-white/5`.
- Tooltip on hover for error: HTML `title` attribute with the error message.
- Sidebar container: `flex flex-col w-48 bg-sidebar border-r border-border h-screen`.
- Each row: `cursor-pointer px-3 py-2 flex items-center gap-2 hover:bg-white/5 transition-colors`.

Deliverable
- `components/StageSidebar.tsx` — client component for pipeline stage navigation with live status badges.

Implementation assumptions (explicit)
- Status polling uses simple `fetch` — no SWR or React Query.
- Initial stage statuses default to `not_started` before first poll completes.

Please produce production-ready prompt content that will generate the module consistent with the above.
